[DhtmlXQ_comment0]op ldz c2 51 ccprr lt side h vs sch 7pa||第51局中炮边马过河车对屏风马7卒 ||||ECCO：C19 中炮過河車左邊馬對屏風馬||ECCO：C19 Central cannon with pawn ranked chariot and left side horse vs screen horse defense[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment9]As can be seen, after red advances the chariot, the basic formation of this opening is now set: red's central cannon with pawn ranked chariot and left side horse variation vs black's screen horse defense with 7th pawn advancement.||This opening was very popular in the 1950's and 60's and gradually reached its peak in the 1970's.  It fell out of favor to the other cc variations.||But in today's world, more and more players are starting to pick it up again and has thus far injected new life into this opening. ||It can be seen now and then in the National Competitions.[/DhtmlXQ_comment9]
[DhtmlXQ_comment10]This is a must make move for black.||Plying C8=9 or P3+1 now would allow red to increase his advantage in the game.||Jim: pls click on the variation below.[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
